/**
 * Product Manager Dashboard — FME (Feature Management & Experimentation).
 *
 * Prototype generated by designAI's /design-prototype from the Figma frame
 * "Developer Dashboard" (node 248:2313, the Split-style PM dashboard), rebuilt
 * in the Harness Canary visual language and dropped into the real app shell
 * (left nav + main content, chat zone collapsed) per the attached reference.
 *
 * Primary intent: the "Impression Distribution over time" panel is INTERACTIVE.
 * The slider scrubs a 12-month timeline; the donut, its legend percentages, and
 * the center date all update to the scrubbed month (→ honest status — the chart
 * reflects the selected point in time, never a hopeful default).
 *
 * System honesty note: @harnessio/ui ships NO chart component (verified against
 * the 160-component manifest — `Chart` does not exist, and `Legend` is a form
 * fieldset legend). The donut, sparklines, and trend line are therefore custom
 * SVG — the one off-system surface here. They're driven by the real
 * `--cn-comp-data-viz-*` tokens (01-blue / 02-purple / 05-indigo / 07-cyan) so
 * color still re-themes and survives light/dark, and every series is paired with
 * a text label + value (→ color is never the only signal). Everything else is a
 * real @harnessio/ui component and verifies clean against the manifest.
 */

